The Presidential Taskforce on COVID-19 has disclosed that the next line of action regarding the easing of lockdown will be disclosed on Tuesday. Boss Mustapha, Secretary to the Government of the Federation and Chairman of the taskforce stated this after meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari. Buhari’s Personal Assistant on New Media, Bashir Ahmad disclosed this in a tweet. “Today is the last day of Nigeria’s phase II of the eased lockdown, members of the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 briefed and submitted their recommendations to the President for approval, the next lines of action will be announced tomorrow, SGF Boss Mustapha discloses,” Ahmad wrote. Recall that the task force had met with Buhari to brief him on updates of the committee in containing the spread of COVID-19. Buhari had on June 1, lifted the ban on religious gathering across Nigeria but said schools should remain closed. Tomorrow, Tuesday, June 30, will make it one month since Buhari made the decision.